lu.uni.geko.weaver
Class Weaver

java.lang.Object
  lu.uni.geko.common.AbstractModelTransformer<org.eclipse.emf.common.util.URI>
      lu.uni.geko.weaver.Weaver

public class Weaver
extends AbstractModelTransformer<org.eclipse.emf.common.util.URI>

A facade for initiating the weaving process for a base, pointcut and advice model using a mapping from pointcut to advice elements. This class initiates all steps required for weaving and handles the involved parameters but it has to be used according to the protocol mentioned in its constructor.

Constructor Detail

Weaver

public Weaver(org.eclipse.emf.common.util.URI baseMURI,
              org.eclipse.emf.common.util.URI adviceMURI,
              N2NMap<org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject,org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject> pc2AvN2NMap)
Constructs a new Weaver using the given base model URI, the given advice model URI and the given mapping from pointcut to advice elements.

Attention: In order to work as expected an Weaver has to be used according to the following protocol:
  Weaver weaver = new Weaver(baseMURI, ...);
  URI wovenMURI = weaver.copyBaseToWovenMURI();
  // perform the join point detection using the new result resource that contains a copy of the base
  ...
  List joinPoints = detectJoinpoints(pcMURI, wovenMURI, ...);
  // this ensures that the result of the join point detection refers to the copied base elements
  // and not to the original elements of the base
  weaver.setJoinPoints(joinPoints);
  weaver.transform();

Parameters:
baseMURI - the URI of the base model
adviceMURI - the URI of the advice model
pc2AvN2NMap - the mapping from pointcut to advice elements
